# AI Financial Document Analyzer 📊🤖

A **production-ready AI system** that analyzes financial PDF documents and generates structured insights such as revenue, profit, risks, and investment recommendations using **Google Gemini AI**, **FastAPI**, **Redis**, **Celery**, and **SQLite**.

This system supports **asynchronous background processing**, **concurrent requests**, and **persistent storage of analysis results**.

---

# 🚀 Features

* 📄 Upload financial PDF documents
* 🤖 AI-powered analysis using Google Gemini
* ⚡ Asynchronous processing using Redis + Celery
* 🗄 Database storage using SQLite
* 🌐 REST API using FastAPI
* 🔄 Concurrent request handling (queue-based worker model)
* 📊 Retrieve analysis results anytime
* 🧩 Modular and production-ready architecture

---

# 🏗 Architecture

```
User
 │
 ▼
FastAPI Server
 │
 ▼
Redis Queue
 │
 ▼
Celery Worker
 │
 ▼
Gemini AI Analyzer
 │
 ▼
SQLite Database
 │
 ▼
Result API
```

---

# 📁 Project Structure

```
financial-document-analyzer/
│
├── main.py              # FastAPI API server
├── worker.py            # Celery background worker
├── ai_analyzer.py       # Gemini AI integration
├── tools.py             # PDF text extraction
├── database.py          # SQLite database logic
│
├── requirements.txt     # Python dependencies
├── .env                 # Environment variables
│
├── data/                # Uploaded PDFs
├── analysis.db          # SQLite database
│
└── README.md
```

---

# ⚙️ Technologies Used

* FastAPI
* Google Gemini AI
* Redis
* Celery
* SQLite
* Python
* LangChain PDF Loader
* Uvicorn

---

# 🧠 How It Works

1. User uploads financial PDF via API
2. FastAPI saves file and creates database record
3. Task is sent to Redis queue
4. Celery worker processes document
5. Gemini AI analyzes document
6. Result is stored in SQLite database
7. User retrieves result via API

---

# 📦 Installation & Setup

## 1. Clone repository

```
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/financial-document-analyzer.git

cd financial-document-analyzer
```

---

## 2. Create virtual environment

```
python -m venv .venv

.venv\Scripts\activate
```

---

## 3. Install dependencies

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## 4. Setup environment variables

Create `.env` file:

```
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
```

Get API key:
https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey

---

# 🧰 Install Redis (Windows)

Download:

https://github.com/tporadowski/redis/releases

Extract and run:

```
redis-server.exe
```

---

# ▶️ Run the system

Open 3 terminals:

---

## Terminal 1 — Start Redis

```
redis-server
```

---

## Terminal 2 — Start Celery worker

Windows requires solo pool:

```
celery -A worker worker --pool=solo --loglevel=info
```

---

## Terminal 3 — Start FastAPI

```
uvicorn main:app --reload
```

---

# 🌐 API Documentation

Open:

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
```

---

# 📤 Upload document endpoint

POST

```
/analyze
```

Form Data:

```
file: PDF file
query: analysis request
```

Response:

```
{
  "analysis_id": 1,
  "status": "processing"
}
```

---

# 📥 Get result endpoint

GET

```
/result/{analysis_id}
```

Example:

```
/result/1
```

Response:

```
{
  "status": "completed",
  "result": "Financial analysis..."
}
```

---

# 💾 Database Schema

Table: analyses

| Column   | Type    |
| -------- | ------- |
| id       | INTEGER |
| filename | TEXT    |
| query    | TEXT    |
| result   | TEXT    |
| status   | TEXT    |

---

# 🔄 Queue Worker Model (Bonus Feature)

This project uses:

* Redis as message broker
* Celery as background worker

Benefits:

* Non-blocking API
* Concurrent request handling
* Scalable architecture
* Production ready

